@{b}CLOSE()@{ub}

Usage:@{b}CLOSE(file)@{ub}

Closes the file specified by the given logical name. The returned value is a
boolean success flag, and will be 1 unless the specified file was not open.

Example:
@{fg shine}
        say close('input')              ==>1
@{fg text}
